If you are in a relationship, it is not unusual to give your partner a pet name, such as bae, baby, my love, boo, sweetheart. But, reality TV star Tochi has expressed distaste for ladies calling a grown man ‘baby’ as a pet name. For the former BBNaija housemate, a grown man can be called any other pet name but not ‘baby’ “Stop calling grown men ‘baby.’ Any other thing but not ‘baby’,” he wrote, accompanied by an angry emoji. Tochi’s comment garnered mixed reactions from social media users. - Advertisement - While many said they enjoy being called ‘baby’ by their partners, others said Tochi was not in a position to tell them what names to call their partners. The ladies said they call baby are not complaining. nedum__001 asked: “Tochi…Is it your baby?….are we complaining?….abi they should start calling us comrades?” charmings_fitness said: “Oga you’re on your own in this o, I’m my girlfriend’s baby biko.”   Bovi: I’ll be marking my birthday weekly     Silence has a golden voice, says Actor Ugezu     Don’t marry if you aren’t a millionaire, Joro Olumofin…   manlike_rex wrote: “Tell your wife.” mhisoby quizzed: “Did they complain to you??” mirabel_aduba stated: “Nobi u go tell me wetin I go do.” veevyane__ queried: “Is it your baby? .. are they complaining?” _baby_chii said: “The same men that will get angry if you start calling them their real names.” officialfinewine5 wrote: “Boring boyfriend don drop quote.” ada_nne25 asked: “Men are you complaining??” leaddyskincare stated: “My husband is my baby.” ayetigbo queried: “Can you imagine… what is your business???” official_vee_hive said: “Don’t take this seriously… even Mitchelle calls Obama baby.. who are you not to accept baby.” the_venue3 wrote: “Abeg make them restart this year I don make mistake.”